= User Stories
As #strong([a member of the team]) working on Ratatoskr, I want the micromouse to be easy to service during development, for example by providing debug data after a run. Further, I want the finished micromouse and maze to be easy and moderately quick to set up and store, because I may want to show it off to friends.

More generally, as #strong([a person interested in making things]) I want to see that it is possible to create something fun and interesting, even with a limited background/knowledge in electronics and embedded programming.

As #strong([the professor]) I'd like parts of the project (or the project as a whole) to be reusable for future group or individual projects. Thus, I want the code and the design to be well-documented and modularized.

As #strong([a viewer of a micromouse competition]) I want the micromouse to perform well and be well-designed and compact. Optionally, it would be nice if the micromouse looked good, for example by incorporating some cosmetic aspects such as the LED matrix.